1. Problem Summary (What was the issue?)

Background / Production Issue

In IPS Web (WAS9_RP branch), the Equifax DIT phone verification call intermittently fails due to:
	•	SocketTimeoutException (read timed out)
	•	ClientRuntimeException
	•	Occasional NullPointerException
	•	Transaction rollback (UnexpectedRollbackException)

These failures originate during the Equifax DIT REST call:
	•	CommonRestServiceImpl.sendInitiateDITRequest(...)
	•	Specifically at the HTTP POST to the Equifax endpoint

Observed Production Impact
	•	When Equifax times out or returns an unexpected response, the application:
	•	Does not properly handle the failure
	•	Allows exceptions or null responses to bubble up
	•	The outer workflow (verifyPhone → getPhoneVerificationResponse) re-invokes the same transaction repeatedly for the same user
	•	This results in:
	•	Infinite retry behavior at the workflow level
	•	Continuous ERROR log entries for the same user/event
	•	Rapid log file growth (1.5 GB – 6.7 GB observed)
	•	Risk of application server disk exhaustion

Root Cause (Code-Level)
	1.	sendInitiateDITRequest:
	•	Logs runtime/network exceptions
	•	Returns null without marking an error state
	2.	verifyPhoneWithEquifaxDIT:
	•	Assumes a non-null response
	•	Calls business logic (evaluateDITOverallDecision) on a null response
	•	Throws NullPointerException
	3.	The outer workflow retries the entire transaction indefinitely because:
	•	No bounded retry guard exists at the workflow level
	•	Failures are not converted into a controlled terminal failure response

