2. What We Were Trying to Fix

Objective of the Fix

Ensure that any Equifax DIT failure (timeout, runtime error, null response, HTTP error) results in:
	•	A single controlled failure
	•	No uncaught runtime exceptions
	•	No infinite workflow re-entry
	•	No log flooding
	•	A deterministic FAIL / REVIEW outcome returned to the workflow

Key Design Changes
	•	Convert Equifax runtime/network failures into a handled error state
	•	Short-circuit the flow when an error occurs
	•	Never evaluate DIT business logic on a null response
	•	Ensure the method returns a failure response instead of throwing

