3. Acceptance Criteria (for the Story)

You can paste this section directly into Jira.

Acceptance Criteria
	1.	Graceful Handling of Equifax Timeouts
	•	When the Equifax DIT service times out or throws a runtime exception:
	•	The application must not throw an unhandled exception
	•	The phone verification flow must return a controlled FAIL response
	•	The workflow must not retry the same transaction indefinitely
	2.	No Infinite Retry / Looping
	•	For a given user and phone verification event:
	•	The Equifax DIT call must be executed at most once per workflow invocation
	•	The system must not continuously re-enter verifyPhone → getPhoneVerificationResponse for the same event
	•	Logs must not grow indefinitely for the same user/event
	3.	Null Response Safety
	•	If the Equifax DIT response is null or malformed:
	•	The system must treat it as an error
	•	No NullPointerException must occur
	•	Business decision logic must not be executed on a null response
	4.	Consistent Failure Result
	•	On Equifax failure (timeout, HTTP error, runtime exception):
	•	Phone verification decision must be set to FAIL (or REVIEW if business rules dictate)
	•	Failure reason must be recorded and persisted where applicable
	•	Downstream workflow must proceed without retrying the same Equifax call
	5.	Logging Behavior
	•	Only a single ERROR log entry should be produced per failed Equifax attempt
	•	Repeated ERROR logs for the same user/event must not occur

